SIMPLE: malign
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: malign
<hw>ma*lign"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>malignus</ets>, for <ets>maligenus</ets>, i. e., of a bad kind or
nature; <ets>malus</ets> bad + the root of <ets>genus</ets> birth, race,
kind: cf. F. <ets>malin</ets>, masc., <ets>maligne</ets>, fem. See
<er>Malice</er>, <er>Gender</er>, and cf. <er>Benign</er>,
<er>Malignant</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having an evil disposition
toward others; harboring violent enmity; malevolent; malicious;
spiteful; -- opposed to <ant>benign</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Witchcraft may be by operation of <qex>malign</qex> spirits.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Unfavorable; unpropitious; pernicious; tending to
injure; <as>as, a <ex>malign</ex> aspect of planets</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Malignant; <as>as, a <ex>malign</ex>
ulcer</as>.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Malign</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Malign
<hw>Ma*lign"</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Maligned</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Maligning</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. L. <ets>malignare</ets>.
See <er>Malign</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <def>To treat with malice; to
show hatred toward; to abuse; to wrong; to injure.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The people practice what mischiefs and villainies they will
against private men, whom they <qex>malign</qex> by stealing their
goods, or murdering them.</q> <rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To speak great evil of; to traduce; to defame; to
slander; to vilify; to asperse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To be envied and shot at; to be <qex>maligned</qex> standing, and
to be despised falling.</q> <rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Malign</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Malign
<hw>Ma*lign"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To entertain malice.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Malignancy</ent>⟦br⟧
